[3] South America
[A] Peru
Date: Sun 20 Jun 2021
Source: Andina [edited]
https://andina.pe/agencia/noticia-peru-coronavirus-cases-total-2026729-849916.aspx


The number of citizens infected with COVID-19 rose to 2 026 729 and the death toll reached 190 202 in Peru as of [Fri 18 Jun 2021], the Ministry of Health (Minsa) has confirmed.

Within this framework, 161 people passed away from the virus on the analyzed day. A total od 11 703 623 samples tested negative for COVID-19 --out of a total of 13 730 352.

It must be noted that 1 982 916 people have been discharged and declared healthy. Other 10 052 were hospitalized.

On the other hand, a total of 6 239 431 vaccine doses have been administered in Peru as of [Sat 19 Jun 2021]. Within this framework, 2 438 319 people have received both doses.

