[4] Israel school related outbreak
Date: Sat 19 Jun 2021
Source: Israel Hayom [in Hebrew, trans. Mod.AS, edited]
https://www.israelhayom.co.il/news/local/article/2370803/


Following an increase in the number of confirmed cases in students at the "Asif" school in Modi'in, the municipality decided to return the mask wearing obligation in the city's educational institutions.

The Modi'in municipality updated yesterday [Fri 18 Jun 2021] that 11 6th-grade students at the school were infected by COVID. Today [Sat 19 Jun 2021] their number has been updated, rising to 15. Also, 2 teachers in the city were found positive for the virus, and 2 family members of students were confirmed infected.

At the same time, 45 children have been confirmed to be infected in Binyamina; the Ministry of Health is examining whether there is a connection to a family that recently returned from abroad, suspecting the involvement of the Indian COVID-19 variant.

The outbreak was discovered thanks to an extensive sampling operation, which began with the 1st sick child at the Cramim school in Binyamina. Following the exposure, more students in different age groups at the school were examined and 9 additional confirmed infected; all but one of whom were symptomatic.

As a result, the sampling was extended to additional schools and this morning [19 Jun 2021] another 35 verified infected - some from the Cramim School and the others from Amirim School. The new cases are under investigation by the Hadera Health Bureau.

All the samples were sent to sequencing at Israel's National Center for Genomic Technologies. As mentioned, there is a preliminary suspicion that the Indian variant is involved.

In a press release, the Ministry of Health calls on the residents of Binyamina to be tested, in order to maintain public health and prevent the spread of the virus in the locality. The Ministry also calls on those put under isolation to fully perform the isolation according to the procedures in general, and among returnees from abroad in particular.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[From Mod.AS: "On 17 June 2021, the Director of Public Health Services, Ministry of Health, Jerusalem published a circular No 496167321 (In Hebrew), titled "Epidemiological Opinion: Extending the Validity of the 'Special Powers Act Confronting the New Corona Virus (Temporary Order), 2020', (hereinafter the Act) and Extension of an Emergency Situation According to the Act". (<tinyurl.com/j4f8z6nb>)

"The (11 pages) document included, among others, a description of a recent event as follows:

"A 6th-grade girl from the city of Modi'in who returned with her parents from abroad, broke isolation and returned to school immediately when back home, later diagnosed as a COVID-19 patient. As of today [Thu 17 Jun 2021], at least 12 out of about 100 contacts of hers have been diagnosed ill (of which 11 children) . Her samples have been highly suspected by the lab as infected by the Indian variant. Final results are still pending. Following the illness, about 360 additional (pupils, teachers, parents of children, etc.) were sampled and about 90 more contacts have been placed in isolation.

"The actual dimensions of the event will become established only during the coming weeks; hopefully, the early intervention, including rapid investigation, extensive sampling and isolation of contacts may lead to a success in reducing the scope of the event.

"This event includes morbidity introduced from abroad, the involvement of a mutant variant with a particularly high infectious potential, non-compliance with isolation requirements, and the rapid spread of morbidity within a group of unvaccinated children which is not vaccinable at the current stage. It clearly illustrates the close connection between the threats outside the borders of the State of Israel and the risk that a single point event may violate the relaxed morbidity, achieved with great effort and a heavy toll paid".

Several take away points here:

1st and foremost is the weaknesses in honor systems that are used upon opening up of restrictions. The index case's family did not follow the requested isolation period and the unvaccinated child returned to school during the incubation period. (Israel's isolation criteria and pre-requisites available at https://www.gov.il/en/departments/guides/corona-quarantine?chapterIndex=9)

2nd, while Israel has succeeded in vaccinating approximately 80% of the adult population and approximately 60% of all citizens https://www.businessinsider.com/israel-vaccinated-most-adults-covid-herd-immunity-2021-6) (56.9% https://bit.ly/3vMlVh88 and 59% https://ourworldindata.org/COVID-vaccinations?country=OWID_WRL~ISR~USA~IND).

Up until recently the focus was on age 16 years and older there remain pockets of unvaccinated. Vaccination recommendations for ages 12-16 are available at https://govextra.gov.il/ministry-of-health/COVID19-vaccine/en-COVID19-vaccines-for-children/ and vaccine is available, there are still the primary and pre-school-aged children who are not being vaccinated as yet. This creates significant "pockets" of susceptibles who are at risk of infection and serve as transmitters. (see section [2] below for more on this topic).

According to a recent Israeli Ministry of Health press release "Nevertheless, since the infection rate in Israel is currently very low, it was recommended that people from high-risk groups be vaccinated, including teenagers who are at high-risk for serious coronavirus illness, teenagers who live with family members who are at high-risk for serious coronavirus illness, as well as for teenagers in families who plan to travel abroad." Press release on vaccination of teenagers 12-16 years of age. https://www.gov.il/en/departments/news/02062021-01).

Other pockets of susceptibles exist in Israel as well and the above outbreak highlights what can happen when the virus is introduced into a pocket of unvaccinated susceptibles.

3rd, travel remains a high risk endeavor for disease transmission. Especially travelling with unvaccinated individuals (including children). The location of travel was not given in the reports we've seen thus far but there are very few countries in the world that have not reported cases. https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/.premium-students-ordered-to-wear-masks-in-central-israel-due-to-local-COVID-outbreak-1.9922073, https://www.jpost.com/health-science/is-israel-on-the-verge-of-a-new-COVID-19-outbreak-671558 (no mention of importation). - Mod.MPP]

