[In the past 24 hours, 7 countries including India (53 009), Brazil (44 178), Colombia (27 818), Indonesia (13 737), Russia (17 611), South Africa (13 155), and Argentina (10 395), have reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 6425 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 18 Jun 2021 to late 19 Jun 2021). A total of 41 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 16 of the 41 countries are from the European region, 7 are from the Americas region, 6 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 4 are from the Western Pacific region, and 3 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 0.54%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 24.9%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show 23.1% decrease in daily reported cases and 21.3% decrease in reported deaths.

